        <h1>Houzz Pro vs. Contractor Foreman (2026)</h1>
        <p>Both serve small contractors. Houzz Pro is polished and client-facing. Contractor Foreman packs in features at a lower price. Here's how to pick.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">

        <p>Houzz Pro and Contractor Foreman are both aimed at small to mid-size contractors, but they're built around different core values. Houzz Pro prioritizes a polished client experience, professional presentation, and lead generation for residential contractors. Contractor Foreman prioritizes feature breadth and affordability — it's the most features-per-dollar platform in the small contractor market. The right choice depends heavily on your type of work and what you value most.</p>

        <h2>Quick comparison</h2>
        <div class="quick-table">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th></th><th>Houzz Pro</th><th>Contractor Foreman</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Pricing</strong></td><td>$99–$199/mo</td><td>$49–$299/mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Lead generation</strong></td><td>⭐ Houzz marketplace exposure</td><td>None</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Client portal</strong></td><td>⭐ Polished, client-facing</td><td>Basic</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Proposals/estimates</strong></td><td>⭐ Visual, branded</td><td>Functional</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Time tracking</strong></td><td>Basic</td><td>⭐ Included</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Scheduling</strong></td><td>Basic</td><td>⭐ More detailed</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Job costing</strong></td><td>Basic</td><td>⭐ More detailed</td></tr>
